ou very much for your efforts on behalf of LOLITA.3 Would you mind taking care of the MS until you hear from me again, which will be soon? I want to have the thing published and am looking for an agent. Incidentally, would you happen to know of one who would undertake to place the book? I would be willing to let him have up to twenty five percent.





Sincerely,

Vladimir Nabokov





TO: WALLACE BROCKWAY

CC, 1 p.





General Delivery

Taos, New Mexico

July 25, 1954

